What is Beeline?
===============

Hive comes with Hiverserver2 which is a server interface and has its own command line interface (CLI) known as Beeline.

* Beeline is used to connect to Hive and run HiveQL queries

* Beeline is a JDBC client

Using Beeline to Connect to Remote Hive
========================================
!connect jdbc:hive2://m02.itversity.com:10000/;auth=noSasl

You will replace m02.itversity.com with your remote server
By default, HiveServer2 runs on port 10000.

